"Valentinov's expecting you",' said the voice with a laugh, sang out a German 'good-bye' and vanished behind the click of its trapdoor. For several moments Mrs. Luzhin sat there thinking and then called herself a fool. She should have explained first of all that Luzhin no longer played chess. Valentinov... Only now did she remember the visiting card she had found in the opera hat.